Processors in H3 are just like in H1 -- they can take optional 
DecideRules that control whether they run or are skipped; only the 
syntax is a little different.

But, by looking at the &#39;scope&#39; of our bundled example configuration, and 
the Spring 2.5 &#39;container&#39;/XML format docs [1], it should be easy for 
you to set up -- especially if you&#39;re already comfortable talking about 
the (custom) H1 XML format!

- Gordon @ IA

[1] http://static.springsource.org/spring/docs/2.5.x/reference/beans.html



